    "source_sections": {
      "references": "",
      "remarks": "The connection to unit fractions comes from the observation that $\\frac{1}{a}+\\frac{1}{b}$ is a unit fraction if and only if $a+b\\mid ab$.\n\nWouter van Doorn has given an elementary argument that proves that if $A\\subseteq \\{1,\\ldots,N\\}$ has $\\lvert A\\rvert \\geq (25/28+o(1))N$ then $A$ must contain $a\\neq b$ with $a+b\\mid ab$ (see the discussion in [301]).\n\nSee also [302]."
    },
    "source_state": "open",
    "tags": [
      "number theory",
      "unit fractions"
    ]
  },
